In his weekly address, the President sends prayers to those affected by Hurricanes Harvey and Irma and assures that the government is coordinating closely with local authorities to provide assistance. He highlights the 230th anniversary of the signing of the Constitution and emphasizes the importance of the government's power being vested in the citizens. The President calls for a recommitment to the Founding Principles and the defense of freedom, urging loyalty to the Republic and its citizens. He concludes by urging allegiance to the flag, devotion to the country, and love for one another.